annotation.TEXT: NOOOOO!!! YOSHI!!! Stupid paraduders... Well, anyway, here's the pipe you can enter.
Oh, and the second Yoshi coin is just a little ways to the right of the first one. Just be careful of the fireballs.
There's more multi-coin blocks, and then the pipe leading out of here.
You can get the first Yoshi coin here, which is partially submerged. Note that grabbing it will take out a small chunk of the water, which could affect your movement while swimming.
Hello, and welcome back to Chaos CompleXX! It's time to go "in the air of koopa"!
Well, I was done with that level anyway. Now, let's move on. Hmm... I think there'll be a "water level here".

Yeah, I think the water is partially made of lava here. You can still swim in the water okay, but since fireballs life in the waters here, keep watching and watch out for them to pop out, or they will burn you!
Aw, nuts! Well, looks like I'm joining that duder...
And right near this message box, we can already see the third, fourth, and fifth Yoshi coins!
I'll just take this Yoshi coin I skipped earlier. Then, hit these two turn blocks to find a star!
YES!!! 1-life combo! Woo-hoo!
This pipe over here is where you'd eventually come out if you entered the previous pipe back there.
That opens up what I think will be a water level, but I'm going to go back and show off that bonus room I skipped before.
Now, the arrows point to the right, but go left first, watching out for fireballs and duders. Also, don't kill the duders, yet.
Make sure you actually go down the pipe instead of sliding off of it! (Good thing I reacted in time before I sank too far!)
Ow! Whatever...
Hahaha! Well, that's interesting! Somehow I got that duder to perform the block cloning glitch! Unfortunately, he died just afterwards...
Collect Yoshi coins 6 through 8 here, and try not to fall. There are a few yellow blocks below these moving platforms, but they aren't everywhere, so you might not land on them if you slip.
Now, I can blast through the duders and fireballs without worry for a while!
It shouldn't take long for me to get there, so I'm not going to speed up any of this footage.
There's lots of coins and note blocks, and a few blue duders in here too. You can thwack them by bouncing off a nearby note block at the right time. Also, if you brought a shell in with you...
Watch out for this paraduder and then grab the last few Yoshi coins. I think that's every Yoshi coin, which makes 14 total in this level if I counted right! (If I missed any, let me know!)

There's a couple of multi-coin blocks, but I'm not going to spend all day on them. Also, there's a somewhat obvious secret passage under the rectangle of floating coins you can go through to reach the water below.
Take a mighty leap up here and you can land on these high up mushroom platforms. However, I don't think anything is hidden up there. (If there is something, let me know!)

Here's a midpoint and a flower that you can grab if you want, followed by edited-in footage of me hitting this message box, because I somehow skipped it when I first played through the level, and didn't realize it until later.
After the message box is another falling fuzzy, but I was running full speed and still didn't hit it, so it's probably nothing to worry about unless you're doing some unusual screen scrolling here.
In the meantime, I'll just call them "duders" for the duration of this episode.
If you want, you could use those yellow blocks to avoid the paraduders above. Also, you can enter the pipe, but it's a good idea to skip it for now (I will show it later, though).
Uh, oh! There's a "fight against enemy" up ahead, which I'll handle next time!
Okay, let's see if I can get a 1-up from this invincibility combo...
There's coins in most of these turn blocks, so hit them if you really like coins.
OH, COME ON!!! SERIOUSLY?!?!
You can swim all the way to the left, under the pipe, but that's about it.
Whoa, Yoshi! Watch out!
Ow! I guess I failed to keep watching and watch out.
Alright, there's the goal. Now, I only need 2 bonus stars for a bonus game, so I could hit the goal tape just about anywhere and get it...
Now, let's see if I can do the block cloning glitch without dying like that duder did...
Demo count: 5
If you take the upper route here, you'll encounter a few paraduders, but they shouldn't be a big deal. Also, there's a fuzzy, but it vanishes shortly after appearing, so it's not a threat.
Okay, let's try that again and NOT crash into that duder in a horribly embarrassing way!
And, yep, as this message indicates, there are a lot off yoshis Coins in this levl, and you can colect them for many lifes!
Also, at least I still have my reserve feather...
Now, the cement blocks here prevent you from getting 50 stars from this goal, so just do the best that you can. You should still be able to get in the upper 20s.
Now, if you took that shortcut from earlier, you'll end up here, right by this message box.

And over here are more paraduders, an upside-down piranha plant, and more Yoshi coins! Now, if you had gone in that pipe earlier after grabbing at least five Yoshi coins, these wouldn't be here, and you'd miss out on getting more 1-ups!
Over here is another entrance to the water in case you somehow didn't see that earlier secret passage. After that, watch out for fires and the sliding duder.
Again, watch out for the fuzzy if you don't have Yoshi.
GAAAMMME!!!
When you're done down here, go through this pipe and you'll come out of that pipe just before midpoint that I pointed out before.

Squash this duder and enter this pipe to reach another bonus room. Oh, and don't worry about the Yoshi coin. I'll get it later. (Actually, whether you grab that Yoshi coin first doesn't matter in this case.)
Eat or stomp or do whatever to these paraduders, and keep going. Don't fall here, or it won't end well for you.
Get some coins and a 1-up (or a new Yoshi if you need one) here.

Still, you want to avoid hitting the fireballs anyway, because you can't kill them, and for some reason, touching them resets your invincibilty kill combo, meaning your next kill will start the combo over at 200 points.
Well, I'll get the bonus game next time for sure!
You can shell jump or fly to take a small shortcut here, like this, but I'm going to go back and take the long way around.
Come on, make it...
Okay, now after dealing with that duder, go over here to find a couple of Yoshi coins. I hope you've hit the yellow switch already!
And there's Yoshi coin number six. I think that's all of them. Well, I guess I'll follow all these oddly placed arrow signs that somehow displace the water in interesting ways...
Okay, 28 sounds good. 30 would've been really nice, but oh, well...

Now, I've been informed that "koopers" in the first level's name is the typo, and "koopas" is actually correct. However, I'm already used to calling them "koopers". Should I continue calling them "koopers", or go with "koopas"? Vote now!
Here's another paraduder that you can play around with.
Watch out for the falling fuzzy right when the level starts! However, Yoshi is immune to it, so if you're riding Yoshi, you're safe.
Demo count: 4
Yeah, if I had taken the time to at least grab the first mushroom here last time, that pitiful death wouldn't have happened.
To be continued...
